name: Corals #3 | Abyssus lampadis
description:
During my search for Corals I stumbled upon an unknown species. I was drawn to it, Maybe it's those lights, slowly drifting away along the slow movement of the abyss. As I got closer, I realized it was an enormous coral formation, the bulb were standing on top of impressive arms. It's probably a type of Anemonae. For documentation purposes I will name it Abyssus Lampadis ( the lamp of the abyss ). the lamps seems to emit a sound, some type of music... I need to go closer to make sure...

Abyssys Lampadis is the third and final piece of the Corals series.

20x20 inches
7500 x 7500px
